Package gov.ca.dsm2.input.model

Class Summary
BoundaryInput The boundary input to the model.
BoundaryInputs  
Channel In DSM2 a channel is an entity representing a stream with a in stream length Channel.getLength(), roughness coefficient (mannings n) Channel.getMannings(), dispersion factor Channel.getDispersion() for water quality constituents It is defined by an id Channel.getId() and its two end nodes, up node Channel.getUpNodeId() and down node Channel.getDownNodeId().
ChannelOutput  
Channels A container for all channels Channels.getChannels() in DSM2 model.
DSM2Model Represents the model as channels Channels, nodes Nodes, reservoirs Reservoirs, gates Gates, outputs Outputs and inputs BoundaryInputs as top level elements.
Gate A gate in the model DSM2Model contained in Gates.
Gates A container for all the Gate objects with ability to retrieve them all Gates.getGates().

Reservoir Represents a reservoir in the model DSM2Model and contained by Reservoirs.

XSection Contains the xsection of a Channel in XSectionLayer layers.
XSectionLayer A layer in the XSection which defines the elevation XSectionLayer.getElevation(), the top width XSectionLayer.getTopWidth(), the wetted perimeter XSectionLayer.getWettedPerimeter(), the area XSectionLayer.getArea()
